Apostle Johnson Suleman of Omega Fire Ministries, has reacted to the death of popular evangelist, Reinhard Bonnke. The German evangelist died in the early hours of Saturday while in the company of his family members. Bonnke’s family, via his official Facebook page wrote: “It is with sorrow that the Bonnke Family would like to announce the passing of our beloved husband, father, and grandfather, Evangelist Reinhard Bonnke. “He passed away peacefully, surrounded by his family, on December 7, 2019.” However, Apostle Suleman recalled the the deceased affected him with his radical passion for evangelism. In a tweet, Suleman wrote: “You affected me so much with your radical passion for evangelism. You finished your assignment and in your lifetime handed over to your successor..rest in peace EVANGELIST REINHARD BONNKE. May we also finish well. Goodnight sir..” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.